        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued September 6 at 4:00PM PDT until September 6 at 4:30PM PDT by NWS Las Vegas NV</headline>
        <description>At 359 PM PDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 10 miles south of
Boulder City, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs and trees.

This severe thunderstorm will impact Highway 95 near the Copper
Mountain Solar Farm.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
